# Catppuccin Mocha dircolors
#
# GNU dircolors database using the Catppuccin Mocha palette
# (https://catppuccin.com/palette), in 24-bit truecolor SGR codes. Loaded
# by dot_zsh.after/06_dircolors.zsh via `dircolors -b ~/.dircolors`, which
# sets $LS_COLORS for GNU ls (see aliases.sh: ls/ll resolve to the
# coreutils gnubin `ls`, not BSD /bin/ls, so LS_COLORS applies on macOS too).
#
# Not tied to the vim/tmux/kitty `.param.color` theme picker -- this file
# always applies once sourced.

